title: President Obama to Travel to New York City | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
September 01, 2011

 



President Obama to Travel to New York City





	WASHINGTON â€“ On Monday, September 19, the President will travel to New York City, returning to Washington, DC, on Wednesday, September 21. While in New York City, the President will participate in the United Nations General Assembly, attend additional bilateral and multilateral meetings on the margins of UNGA, and deliver remarks at the Clinton Global Initiative.
